bioreason_combined:
=== Evidence synthesis ===
1. Domain architecture and fold: The polypeptide is a compact thioredoxin-like enzyme (IPR013766 Thioredoxin domain [1–149]; IPR036249 Thioredoxin-like superfamily [4–147]; IPR036249 Glutaredoxin [1–148]) that is fully overlapped by peroxiredoxin signatures (IPR050924 Thiol-specific peroxidase BCP/PrxQ [3–142]; PRX_BCP [6–143]; IPR000866 Alkyl hydroperoxide reductase subunit C/TSA [2–123]). This architecture encodes a thiol-dependent peroxidase typical of bacterial peroxiredoxins and bacterioferritin-comigratory proteins (bcp). The fold supports reversible cysteine-based redox chemistry and catalyzes reduction of peroxides.

